This paper is about natural language processing and specifically about dependency parsing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses neural networks and parameter sharing, which are topics commonly found in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of LSTM networks, which are a type of recurrent neural network commonly used in natural language processing and other sequence modeling tasks, and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of parsers on different languages, which could fall under the category of natural language engineering (cs.NE).
